---
<a class="demo-link" target="_blank" href="http://www.algolia.com">Algolia</a>
<div class="reveal">
  <div class="slides">
    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <h3>A record is an object you add to an index and want to search for. It can contain any number of attributes.</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <pre class="code-sample"><code data-trim data-noescape>
{
  "name": "Apple - iPhone 5c 8GB Cell Phone (Unlocked) - Blue",
  "description": "A6 chip. 8MP iSight camera. 4-inch Retina display. Ultrafast LTE wireless. iPhone 5c has the things that made iPhone 5 an amazing phone &#8212; and more, including iOS 7. All in a completely new design that feels great in your hand.",
  "brand": "Apple",
  "categories": [
    "Cell Phones",
    "Unlocked Cell Phones",
    "All Unlocked Cell Phones"
  ],
  "hierarchicalCategories": {
    "lvl0": "Cell Phones",
    "lvl1": "Cell Phones > Unlocked Cell Phones",
    "lvl2": "Cell Phones > Unlocked Cell Phones > All Unlocked Cell Phones"
  },
  "type": "So unlocked hardware",
  "price": 609.99,
  "price_range": "500 - 2000",
  "image": "http://img.bbystatic.com/BestBuy_US/images/products/9783/9783432_sb.jpg",
  "url": "http://www.bestbuy.com/site/apple-iphone-5c-8gb-cell-phone-unlocked-blue/9783432.p?id=1219435649649&skuId=9783432",
  "free_shipping": true,
  "popularity": 9653,
  "objectID": "9783432"
        }
    </code></pre>
  </section>
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-12">
          <h3>Buidling a searche engine</h3>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-12">
          <p class="text-left text-justify">Integrating a search engine to your platform is a two step process:</p>
          <ul class="list-inline">
            <li><b>Basic settings</b></li>
            <li>
              <ul>
                <li>Declare which attributes you want to make searchable by users and order these attributes by importance</li>
                <li>Communicate business metrics to the search engine, such as popularity measures or other custom metrics that will be included in the search algorithm</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>Ranking Formula</b></li>
            <ul>
              <li>Algorithm and rules that will power the ranking formula of the search engine</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <section><h1>Basic settings</h1></section>
    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row ">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <h3>Declare which attributes you want to make searchable by users and order these attributes by importance</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row ">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <%= image_tag "basic_settings_attributesToIndex.png", class: "img-rounded" %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row ">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <h3>Communicate business metrics to the search engine, such as popularity measures or other custom metrics that will be included in the search algorithm</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row ">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <%= image_tag "basic_settings_customRanking.png", class: "full_frame_img" %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section><h3><%= link_to 'Search for TV Shows', 'https://www.algolia.com/demo/autocomplete' %></h3></section>
  </section>
  <section>
    <section><h1>Ranking formula</h1></section>
    <section>
      <div class="container">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                  <h3>Picture a set of data including colors, shapes and popularity measures</h3>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col">
                  <%= image_tag "data_step_1.png" %>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
    </section>
        <section>
          <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                <h3>Most search engines use a coefficient-based approach and rank results based on a unique float value that is hard, if not impossible, to decipher. </h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col">
                <%= image_tag "formula.png" %>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div></section>
           <section>
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                    <h3>We built a tie-breaking algorithm. We sort results using rules that we are going to consider one after the other. </h3>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col">
                    <%= image_tag "tie_breaking.png", class: "full_frame_img" %>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section>
           <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                <h3>Rule n°1: Sort by color. </h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col">
                <%= image_tag "data_step_2.png"%>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div></section>
          <section>
           <div class="container">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                  <h3>Rule n°2: Sort by shape. </h3>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col">
                  <%= image_tag "data_step_3.png"%>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
          <section>
           <div class="container">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                  <h3>Rule n°3: Include custom ranking: popularity. </h3>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col">
                  <%= image_tag "data_step_4.png"%>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
          <section>
            <div class="container">
              <div class="row div col-xs-12"><h3>The rules inside a ranking formula:</h3></div>
              <div class="row div col-xs-12">
                <table class="table">
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>Typo</b></td>
                    <td>Does the results contain typing mistakes?</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>Words</b></td>
                    <td>How many words typed by the user are matching in the record?</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>Proximity</b></td>
                    <td>How physically near are the query words in the records?</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>Attribute</b></td>
                    <td>In which attributes are the words matching? How important is this attribute?</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>Exact</b></td>
                    <td><em>Butter</em> or <em>Butter</em>fly? Should we rank higher words that match exactly without any suffix?</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>Custom ranking</b></td>
                    <td>How to include business information?</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>Geo-based search</b></td>
                    <td>How to include physical distance in the ranking formula</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr></tr>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
          <section>
           <div class="container">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                  <h3>Out how 5,040 ordering possibilities (7!), our research concluded that this ranking formula is the most relevant on 99% of use-cases.</h3>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col">
                  <%= image_tag "ranking_formula.png", class: "full_frame_img"%>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h1>References</h1>
  </section>
  </div>
</div>

